Description:
An apartment with the extra space you’ve been looking for!
Light filled with large floor to ceiling windows this apartments generous open plan living area offers room to comfortably enjoy inner city living without comprising on space. The open plan design allows for separate living and dining zones with room to entertain with access to a private balcony. The generous kitchen includes excellent storage with moveable island bench, gas cooking & dishwasher, two double bedrooms both feature built in robes and East facing aspects, central bathroom with lots of storage, separate European laundry, linen cupboard, reverse cycle heating/cooling, secure video intercom entry, basement car park & storage cage complete the package. As a resident, you will enjoy access to a fully equipped gymnasium, hot tubs and roof top entertaining area with panoramic views of the Bay to Melbourne’s CBD.
Insights: 516/32 Bray Street, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2018 and 233 other 2 bedroom unit in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Description:
A Striking Apartment In South Yarra's Heart
This architecturally designed “Longford” apartment offers a trendy lifestyle as Toorak Road cafes, Chapel Street shopping, South Yarra train station, Royal Botanic Gardens, trams and Fawkner Park are all at your fingertips.
With a secure intercom entrance, this second floor apartment presents an ultra stylish open plan living area which flows out to an expansive terrace that is brilliant for entertaining!
A gourmet contemporary kitchen serves in style with stainless steel Miele cooking appliances, an integrated Fisher & Paykel dishwasher and an integrated Fisher & Paykel fridge whilst a generous sun filled bedroom with a walk in robe boasts access to the outdoor terrace.
A central stylish bathroom with a European laundry, a secure basement car space, a storage cage and a split system heating/air conditioning unit are additional advantages to this striking designer apartment which offers a lock-up and go lifestyle to envy.
One of only 36, this boutique apartment has been masterfully designed by “Skematics Architects” and nothing has been overlooked in the pursuit of excellence. Enjoy the cafe lifestyle!
Insights: 206/57 Toorak Road, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2018.

Description:
Consummate Style - Enviable Lifestyle
A rendered façade gives no indication of the inspired interior design of this contemporary split-level town residence. The stunning interior features strategically positioned windows providing a gallery-like feel with loads of internal natural light. Recently refurbished, the home features a downstairs bedroom and bathroom, plus a living room with OFP, dining with a sleek timber, granite and Euro appointed kitchen and adjacent laundry; all surrounding a northern, central courtyard. Whilst upstairs has a north-facing retreat, a further two bedrooms, main with WIR and ensuite, a family bath and powder room plus a study opening to a balcony. Other features include underfloor & central heating, split-system R/C air conditioning, and double garage/storage with secure internal access.
The value and appeal of this property is underpinned by its vibrant lifestyle location close to Hawksburn Village, Chapel Street and Toorak Road - as well as quick access to the CBD, public transport options with Hawksburn station, Malvern and Toorak Road trams plus parklands and a choice of leading schools.
Insights: 7 Joy Street, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2018 and 61 other 3 bedroom house in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Description:
Sophisticated Living in a Boutique Apartment
Innovatively designed to facilitate the perfect blend of a relaxed yet luxurious lifestyle and free flowing indoor/outdoor living and entertaining zones, this stunning ground floor apartment of palatial proportions is a haven of tranquillity and privacy in a premier South Yarra address. The spacious layout incorporates a fitted study area, a vast living and dining domain which merges to an undercover courtyard, an impeccable open plan kitchen equipped with stainless steel appliances and granite benchtops, two double bedrooms both with built in robes, a spotless fully tiled bathroom with separate bath and marble vanity plus a powder room. Timber flooring throughout, a European laundry, basement carspace, split system heating/cooling, storage room, ceiling fan and video intercom entrance are just some of the welcome additions as is a position within walking distance of the glorious Fawkner Park and mere footsteps to Toorak Road trams, cafes and shops.

Description:
Apartment living at its best
House-like spaces, 3 stunning terraces and an iconic river-side location merge for outstanding effect in this elegant "Yarra Grand" apartment. Positioned on the 4th floor for a unique combination of leafy privacy and views stretching across the Yarra to the far north/easterly horizon, this 3 bedroom/2 bathroom home offers an extraordinary apartment experience in an exclusive Mirvac development metres from the river's edge and surrounded by the delights of Toorak Rd, Chapel St and Royal Botanic Gardens. Wine and dine throughout a sun-filled floorplan where an ensemble of free-flowing living and entertaining areas radiate around a spacious, granite kitchen. Relax, chase the sun, soak up the views of the communal gardens or watch the passing parade on the Yarra from 3 superb terraces providing impressive al fresco accompaniment to this lovely home. Additional highlights include tiled entrance, well-zoned bedrooms (all open to terraces, main in own wing with BIRs and ensuite), ducted heating/cooling, separate laundry, lift, intercom entrance plus 2 car basement parking and storage unit.

Description:
Designer Living in the Heart of South Yarra
Often sought but rarely found is this exclusive opportunity to secure your own apartment within the renowned 'Vogue' tower on Chapel Street. Widely commented as one of Melbourne's landmark designer locations - Chapel Street is second to none in its modern offerings of entertainment, fashion and food. A smart one-bedroom apartment offers contemporary fixtures and fittings with an open plan kitchen hosting ample storage and quality throughout. The generous lounge opens to a balcony which hosts striking views which are the envy of all who consider inner-city living to be the epitome of what Melbourne has to offer. The luxury complex has a pool, spa, sundeck, steam room, sauna, gym, tennis court and lawns. The property offers direct lift access into the Vogue Shopping Centre meaning the best of Chapel Street is literally on your doorstep. Whether you're in the market for a strong investment or a new designer residence don't delay- this wonderful property won't last long.

Three Bedrooms, Art-Deco, Block of Four
Generous proportions, private outlooks and Art Deco period charm deliver a welcoming ambiance in this character filled first floor apartment. Enjoying an elevated position in a tightly held boutique development of just four apartments, this roomy three bedroom abode with an undercover balcony features a long hallway, three enormous king size bedrooms, spacious bathroom with laundry facilities, separate kitchen/meals area with additional space for a cosy entertaining corner or dining table. Boasting the very best of modern day comforts such as off street parking, ducted heating, multiple split system units, rear access, hall storage and plantation shutters throughout whilst retaining key period hallmarks such as timber floorboards, high ceilings and picture rails. Capitalise on a top location next to Toorak Road and Chapel Street cafes, restaurants, trams, cinemas, shops, South Yarra Station and Prahran Market.

In a superb position on the edge of iconic Chapel Street, this boutique modern apartment ticks all the boxes for homebuyers and astute investors alike. 14/102 Millswyn Street, South Yarra
This Blue-Chip investment, first home or city pad is in one of South Yarra’s best streets, with the Royal Botanic Gardens at one end and Fawkner Park at the other. Offering security entry, this apartment overlooks the rooftops of some of Melbourne’s best real estate.

Who wants to live or own a fabulous entry level, blue chip apartment in the centre of the universe?

This highly desirable designer apartment is surrounded by inner city amenities including schools, parks and numerous public transport options and would be ideally suited to either a first home owner or the astute investor seeking attractive rental returns.

The list of special features includes a concealed laundry, extra-large pantry, ducted heating, double basement parking plus an extra-large storage cage, secure video intercom and access to a fully-equipped gym.
